ust. Coastal areas dominate with over 2,500 mm per season, significantly outperforming the Vidarbha and Marathwada regions.\n* **Model Performance:** The Random Forest Regressor achieved an $R^2$ of 0.99, proving that temperature extremes and air pressure are near-perfect predictors of monthly averages.2026 Mumbai Forecast: Temperatures are projected to peak at ~30.5°C in May and dip to a seasonal low of ~25°C in January.","metadata":{}}]}